Tim ventured into the real estate business at the early age of 23 right after he graduated with his honor degree in Business Information System in year 2008. Having completed his internship program with the Sunway Group, he realized that the ordinary, routine working life is not what his heart yearns for as he wanted more time flexibility and mobility. Tim also has a greater desire for all beautiful houses he sets his eyes on and it was that burning passion in him that ultimately led him into the real estate profession.Indeed the first 2 years into the business was a true struggle and a steep learning curve to endure due to the lack of experience, knowledge and of course, limited savings to sustain himself. Being young and with no prior sales experiences, he strived hard to gain his customers’ confidence to entrust him with their million dollar worth of properties to sell or rent. Hard work and persistency were his only bullets to sustain in this highly competitive industry. He also understood the magnitude of providing excellent customer service in order to achieve customer satisfaction and long term business referrals.The year of 2010 marks his first achievement of the company sales target and he was one of the youngest top achievers in the company. He has since then maintained his Top Achiever position until today and eventually made his 1st RM1million at the age of 29 years old. Tim was promoted to Senior Real Estate Negotiator and has become a property investor himself, too. Tim took on the challenging role of a Team Leader in 2015 and together with his partner, Kelvin Lee, they established their team known as the Glow Division recently where he generously shares his experiences and business strategies with the team mates with the vision of learning, improving and succeeding together. Tim also consistently motivates and encourages the team with regular brainstorming workshops to generate new marketing and sales ideas and strategies to stay competent in the market.Amidst the hectic schedule, Tim has also completed his Diploma in Estate Management and registered as a Probationary Estate Agent for 2 years and thereafter as a Registered Estate Agent with the Board of Valuers, Appraisers and Estate Agents Malaysia.

Accompany buyers during visits to and inspections of property, advising them on the suitability and value of the homes they are visiting.
	

Prepare documents such as representation contracts, purchase agreements, closing statements, deeds and leases.
	

Confer with escrow companies, lenders, home inspectors, and pest control operators to ensure that terms and conditions of purchase agreements are met before closing dates.
	

Interview clients to determine what kinds of properties they are seeking.
	

Coordinate property closings, overseeing signing of documents and disbursement of funds.
	

Generate lists of properties that are compatible with buyers' needs and financial resources.
	

Contact property owners and advertise services to solicit property sales listings.
	

Arrange for title searches to determine whether clients have clear property titles.
	

Display commercial, industrial, agricultural, and residential properties to clients and explain their features.
	

Review property listings, trade journals, and relevant literature, and attend conventions, seminars, and staff and association meetings to remain knowledgeable about real estate markets.
	

Coordinate appointments to show homes to prospective buyers.
	

Answer clients' questions regarding construction work, financing, maintenance, repairs, and appraisals.
	

Advise sellers on how to make homes more appealing to potential buyers.
	

Investigate clients' financial and credit status to determine eligibility for financing.
	

Develop networks of attorneys, mortgage lenders, and contractors to whom clients may be referred.
	

Inspect condition of premises, and arrange for necessary maintenance or notify owners of maintenance needs.
	

Conduct seminars and training sessions for sales agents to improve sales techniques.
	

Appraise properties to determine loan values.
	

Evaluate mortgage options to help clients obtain financing at the best prevailing rates and terms.
	

Arrange meetings between buyers and sellers when details of transactions need to be negotiated.
	

Rent or lease properties on behalf of clients.
	

Secure construction or purchase financing with own firm or mortgage company.
	

Solicit and compile listings of available rental properties.
	

Review plans for new construction with clients, enumerating and recommending available options and features.
	

Visit properties to assess them before showing them to clients.
	

Locate and appraise undeveloped areas for building sites, based on evaluations of area market conditions.
	

Contact utility companies for service hookups to clients' property.

As a Valuation Executive before my registration, my work comprises of inspection, measurement and survey of property, checking on planning and documents of titles, collecting and analyzing sales evidence of form opinion of value and drafting reports.  This will be followed by confirming or discussion with the Registered Valuer prior to the finalization of the report.

During inspection, I was trained to detect and check any apparent defects in the building such as cracks, poor maintenance and dilapidation, which may result depreciation of the buildings.

Lastly, I was trained in writing good professional reports by emphasizing on sentence construction, consistency, and headings, clarifications on assumptions and evidences and recommendations so as to keep the report simple and concise.
